cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on scheduling and voltage/speed assignments on MPSoCs, which falls under the domain of computer architecture. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with scheduling tasks on MPSoCs, which can be considered a form of parallel computing. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper uses realistic embedded system benchmarks to evaluate the proposed algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with optimizing energy consumption in a system (MPSoCs) with constraints (global deadline, precedence constraints). 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper aims to minimize energy consumption while meeting a global deadline, which can be seen as a performance metric.
